Review:
As most of the better hotels in Jamshedpur were over booked, I booked this hotel on-line, purely going by its name. An officer from Tata Steel, Jamshedpur, who came to drop me at the hotel, had a tough time locating the hotel. I stayed here from 20-23 Nov.
PROS - Fairly large rooms, free wi-fi, complimentary breakfast, passable toiletries; a good touch was a sachet of Almond Drop hair oil.The Hotel has a bar attached; room service is good; food is good and tastefully prepared; breakfast is OK.
CONS - Located in the midst of a bustling market and not very pleasant surroundings; only conveyance from / to the hotel is by share autos (an experience, less said the better); Hotel arranges taxis but are very expensive; Air conditioner was so noisy that it disturbs your sleep. It was more of noise and less of comfortable temperature;
